{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lesson 11: Add CRUD Operations for WorkOrders","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this lesson, you'll add the ability to fetch, create, update, and delete work orders in the turbine-specific page. This involves making API calls to the backend and updating the Redux store accordingly.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning Objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lesson, you will be able to:\n- Fetch work orders from the backend and display them in the turbine dashboard.\n- Structure CRUD methods to interact with Type API endpoints.\n- Create new work orders and send them to the backend.\n- Update existing work orders and reflect those changes in the backend.\n- Delete work orders and remove them from the front-end.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated Time","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lesson will take approximately **30 minutes** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Lab Support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For support, check out the <a href='https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center' target='_blank'>Help Center</a> for information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"------","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 1: Add work orders tab to the turbine-specific page","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this section, you create a new tab on the turbine-specific page to display its corresponding work orders. By the end of this section, you should see the work orders displayed on the page:\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-11/1-work-orders-tab.png\" width=\"400px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 1.1 Fetch turbine-specific `WorkOrder`s","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"First, create a new file `WorkOrderCRUD.ts` in `academyUI/ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/`. This file will contain all the `WorkOrder`-related API calls.\n\nAfter you create <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD.ts\"><code>WorkOrderCRUD.ts</code></a>, copy and paste `fetchWorkOrdersByTurbineId` in the file:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"// CREATE WorkOrderCRUD.ts\n\nexport const fetchWorkOrdersByTurbineId = async (turbineId: string): Promise<any[]> => {\n  // Validate turbineId to prevent filter expression injection\n  const safeIdPattern = /^[A-Za-z0-9_-]+$/;\n  if (!safeIdPattern.test(turbineId)) {\n    throw new Error('Invalid turbineId format');\n  }\n\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WorkOrder/fetch', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      filter: `turbineId == '${turbineId}'`, // only fetch work orders for the specified turbine\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Failed to fetch work orders for turbine');\n  }\n\n  const data = await response.json();\n  return data.objs || [];\n};","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Add the following imports to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>. \n\nThese imports include the new function you just created in `WorkOrderCRUD.ts` and a new component `WorkOrdersTab` that you'll add to turbine-specific page.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\nimport { Tab, Tabs, Snackbar, Alert } from '@mui/material';\nimport { fetchWorkOrdersByTurbineId } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD';\nimport WorkOrdersTab from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/WorkOrdersTab';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Initialize a state variable to store the work orders displayed on the page.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n// ... other code ...\n//  const turbineIdFromState = useSelectedState(turbineDataSelector, (prev: any, next: any) => prev === next);\n\n//  const [turbineData, setTurbineData] = useState({});\n\n    // set state for work orders\n    const [workOrders, setWorkOrders] = useState([]);\n\n//  use effect(() => {\n//    ...\n//  }, [turbineIdFromState]);","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Add the following lines to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n// useEffect(() => {\n//   const fetchData = async () => {\n//     try {\n//       if (turbineIdFromState) {\n//           // Fetch turbine data using CRUD method\n//           const turbineData = await fetchTurbineById(turbineIdFromState);\n//           if (turbineData) {\n//             console.log('Fetched Turbine Data:', turbineData);\n//             setTurbineData(turbineData); // Save fetched data to state\n//           }\n\n          // START: Fetch Work Orders on page load\n          const workOrderData = await fetchWorkOrdersByTurbineId(turbineIdFromState);\n          setWorkOrders(workOrderData);\n          // END\n//     }\n//     } catch (error) {\n//       console.error('Error fetching data:', error);\n//     }\n//   };\n// fetchData();\n// }, [turbineIdFromState]);","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 1.2 Display the work orders in a tab","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Initialize the state variables for the tab.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n// ...\n  // Tabs state\n  const [tabValue, setTabValue] = useState(1); // Default to second tab for convenience during development\n\n  // Tab change on the work orders page\n  const handleTabChange = (event: React.SyntheticEvent, newValue: number) => {\n    setTabValue(newValue);\n  };\n\n// return (...)}","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<style>\n    .c3-a-alert {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: flex-start;\n      padding: 16px 20px;\n      gap: 8px;\n      align-self: stretch;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      border: 1px solid;\n      font-size: 14px;\n      font-style: normal;\n      font-weight: 400;\n      line-height: 150%;\n      margin-bottom: 20px;\n      width: auto;\n    }\n\n    .c3-a-alert-warning {\n      background-color: #fff4e5;\n      border-color: #ffb020;\n      color: rgba(17, 17, 18, 0.95);\n    }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"c3-a-alert c3-a-alert-warning\">\n    <p><b>Note:</b> it is best practice to set the initial tab value to <code>0</code>, which displays the first tab. For the rest of the lesson, you will add functionality to the work orders tab, which is why we set it to <code>1</code>.</p>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the return statement, update the children of the `<Paper>` component:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         {/* 3. Details Tab: Shows metadata and additional information */}\n//         <Paper className=\"wt-tabs-paper\">\n              <Tabs value={tabValue} onChange={handleTabChange} className=\"wt-tabs-container\">\n                <Tab label=\"Turbine Details\" />\n                <Tab label=\"Work Orders\" />\n              </Tabs>\n              {/* Turbine Details Tab */}\n              {tabValue === 0 && <TurbineDetailsTab turbineData={turbineData} />} {/* THIS IS FROM NB 10 */}\n              {/* Work Orders Tab */}\n              {tabValue === 1 && (\n                <WorkOrdersTab\n                  workOrders={workOrders}\n                />\n              )}\n//         </Paper>\n//       ...","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Refresh your user interface. You should see the work orders render under the work orders tab. Since the data is randomly generated, not all turbines have work orders, so you may have to choose a different turbine to view its work orders.\n\nWhen you open a turbine-specific page, you should see a new **Work Orders** tab in the card. \n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-11/2-work-orders.png\" width=\"600px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n\nNote that the buttons are non-functional at the moment. In the next sections, you will add functionality to these buttons to create, update, and delete work orders.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"------","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 2: Create work orders through a modal","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Let's implement some CRUD functionality to the turbine-specific page. We want to enable end-users to create new `WorkOrder` records through the application UI. At the end of this section, you will have implemented a modal that persists new `WorkOrder` records to your application.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 2.1 Add a modal to the turbine-specific page","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"First, import the `WorkOrderModal` component in <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n// Other imports...\nimport WorkOrderModal from \"@c3/app/ui/src/components/WorkOrderModal\";","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Then, initialize a new state variable that controls whether the create modal is open or not. \n\nWe'll also initialize the state for the creation modal to pre-populate the modal with values.\n\nCopy and paste the following snippet into <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//    ...\n//    const handleTabChange = (event: React.SyntheticEvent, newValue: number) => {\n//      setTabValue(newValue);\n//    };\n  \n      const [workOrderOpen, setWorkOrderOpen] = useState(false);\n\n      const [workOrder, setWorkOrder] = useState({\n        title: '',\n        description: '',\n        status: 'Open',\n        assignedTo: '',\n        dueDate: '',\n        estimatedHours: 0\n      });\n\n      // Empty Work orders handlers\n      const handleCreateWorkOrder = () => { \n          setWorkOrderOpen(true);\n      }\n\n      const handleWorkOrderChange = (field: string) => (event: any) => {\n        setWorkOrder((prev) => ({\n          ...prev,\n          [field]: event.target.value,\n        }));\n    };\n    \n//    return (\n//      ...\n//    );\n//  }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>, add the following line to the `WorkOrdersTab` component in the return statement. This adds a handler to open the creation modal.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         {/* 3. Details Tab: Shows metadata and additional information */}\n//         <Paper className=\"wt-tabs-paper\">\n//           ...\n             {/* Work Orders Tab */}\n//           {tabValue === 1 && (\n//             <WorkOrdersTab\n//              workOrders={workOrders}\n                handleWorkOrderOpenModal={handleCreateWorkOrder} // ADD THIS\n//             />)}\n//         </Paper>\n//       ...\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the previous cell, you added functionality to the `+` button in the `WorkOrdersTab` component to open the modal. In the next snippet, add the `WorkOrderModal` component as a sibling to actually display the modal. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n\n// ADD RETURN\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         </Box>\n//\n//        {/* Create Work Order Modal */}\n          <WorkOrderModal\n            open={workOrderOpen}\n            workOrder={workOrder}\n            onChange={handleWorkOrderChange}\n          />\n//       </>\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"#### Verify result","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After implementing the code in this section, refresh the turbine-specific page and select the `+` button to open the work order creation modal. You should see the following:\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-11/2.1-create-modal.png\" width=\"600px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n\nNote that the modal doesn't have any functionality yet. In the next section, you add functionality to the modal to create new work orders.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 2.2 Add functionality to the `WorkOrder` creation modal ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the previous section, you added functionality to display the modal. Now, you will add functionality to write the contents of the modal (a `WorkOrder` record) to your application back-end.\n\nFirst, you'll add a new function that hits the `WorkOrder#create` API. In <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD.ts\"><code>WorkOrderCRUD.ts</code></a>, copy and paste the following code for `createWorkOrder`:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WorkOrderCRUD.ts\n*/\n\nexport const createWorkOrder = async (workOrderData: any): Promise<any> => {\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WorkOrder/create', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'x-request-envelope': 'true',\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      thisArg: workOrderData,\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Failed to create work order');\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n};","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Add the following import to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\nimport { createWorkOrder } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>, add the following to the component body. This code accomplishes the following:\n\n- Initializes the `Snackbar` component state and the message displayed in the `Snackbar`.\n- Handles closing the modal and resets the form.\n- Persists the data in the modal to the `WorkOrder` Type.\n- Updates a single text field in the work order form state (`handleWorkOrderChange`) and handles numeric input fields (`handleNumberChange`). Both of these update the `workOrder` state object with new values as the user types.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//    ...\n//    const handleWorkOrderChange = () => { \n//      ...\n//    }\n\n    // Snackbar state\n    const [snackbarOpen, setSnackbarOpen] = useState(false);\n    const [snackbarMessage, setSnackbarMessage] = useState('');\n\n    const handleWorkOrderClose = () => {\n      setWorkOrderOpen(false);\n      setWorkOrder({\n        title: '',\n        description: '',\n        status: 'Open',\n        assignedTo: '',\n        dueDate: '',\n        estimatedHours: 0\n      });\n    };\n\n    const handleWorkOrderSave = async () => {\n      if (workOrder.title && workOrder.description) {\n        try {\n          // Convert datetime-local format to ISO 8601 for backend\n          const dueDateISO = workOrder.dueDate \n            ? new Date(workOrder.dueDate).toISOString() \n            : null;\n          \n          const workOrderData = {\n            turbineId: (turbineData as any).id,\n            title: workOrder.title,\n            description: workOrder.description,\n            status: workOrder.status,\n            assignedTo: workOrder.assignedTo,\n            estimatedHours: workOrder.estimatedHours,\n            dueDate: dueDateISO,\n            creationDate: new Date().toISOString()\n          };\n\n          await createWorkOrder(workOrderData);\n          // Re-fetch to get properly structured data from the backend\n          const updatedWorkOrders = await fetchWorkOrdersByTurbineId((turbineData as any).id);\n          setWorkOrders(updatedWorkOrders);\n          handleWorkOrderClose();\n        } catch (error) {\n          console.error('Error creating work order:', error);\n        }\n      }\n    };\n\n    const handleNumberChange = (field: string, value: number) => {\n      setWorkOrder({\n        ...workOrder,\n        [field]: value\n      });\n    };\n\n//  return (\n//    ...\n//   );\n// };","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the return statement, add the event handlers to `WorkOrderModal`. Also, add the `Snackbar` component as a sibling to the other components in the return statement.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n// ADD RETURN\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         </Box>\n//\n//        {/* Create Work Order Modal */}\n//        <WorkOrderModal\n//          open={workOrderOpen}\n//          workOrder={workOrder}\n//          onChange={handleWorkOrderChange}\n            onClose={handleWorkOrderClose}\n            onSave={handleWorkOrderSave}\n            onNumberChange={handleNumberChange}\n//         />\n\n          {/* Snackbar */}\n          <Snackbar\n            open={snackbarOpen}\n            autoHideDuration={4000}\n            onClose={() => setSnackbarOpen(false)}\n            anchorOrigin={{ vertical: 'bottom', horizontal: 'right' }}\n            >\n            <Alert severity=\"success\" onClose={() => setSnackbarOpen(false)} className=\"wt-snackbar-alert\">\n              {snackbarMessage}\n            </Alert>\n          </Snackbar>\n//       </>\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"#### Verify result","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this section, try creating a work order record with the title `Test work order`. You can fill in whatever you want for the rest of the fields. \n\nRun the following cell. You should see the work order you just created along with its associated turbine. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"WorkOrder.fetch({filter: Filter.eq('title', 'Test work order')})","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"------","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 3: Update existing work orders","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this next section, you'll add functionality to update existing work orders existing through the UI.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 3.1 Add CRUD methods to update work orders","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Copy and paste the following code into <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD.ts\"><code>WorkOrderCRUD.ts</code></a>. This adds a new function `upsertWorkOrderData` that hits the `WorkOrder#upsert` API to update existing work orders.\n\nNote that we are hitting the `upsert` and `fetch` APIs separately to ensure we have the most up-to-date version of the work order before attempting to update it. This is to prevent version conflicts, which can occur when multiple users are updating the same record around the same time. By fetching the latest version of the work order right before the update, we minimize the chances of encountering a version conflict.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WorkOrderCRUD.ts\n*/\n\n// ... \n\nexport const upsertWorkOrderData = async (workOrderData: any): Promise<any> => {\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WorkOrder/upsert', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'x-request-envelope': 'true',\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      args: [],\n      missingArgs: [],\n      thisArg: workOrderData,\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Failed to update work order data');\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n};\n\nexport const fetchWorkOrderData = async (workOrderId: string): Promise<any> => {\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WorkOrder/fetch', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      filter: `id == '${workOrderId}'`,\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Failed to fetch work order data');\n  }\n\n  const data = await response.json();\n  if (!data.objs || !data.objs[0]) {\n    throw new Error('No work order data found');\n  }\n\n  return data.objs[0];\n};","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Next, add the following import to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\nimport { upsertWorkOrderData } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD';\nimport {fetchWorkOrderData} from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 3.2 Add functionality to update work orders through the UI","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now that we have the necessary CRUD method to update work orders, let's add functionality to the UI to allow end-users to update work orders.\n\nFirst, we'll initialize the state for the **update** modal to pre-populate the modal with the values of the `WorkOrder` record we're trying to update. Similar to the create modal, We'll also initialize a state variable to control whether the update modal is open or not.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//    ...\n//    \n//    const handleNumberChange = (field: string, value: number) => {\n//      setWorkOrder({\n//        ...workOrder,\n//       [field]: value\n//       });\n//    };\n\n      const [editWorkOrderOpen, setEditWorkOrderOpen] = useState(false);\n      const [editingWorkOrderId, setEditingWorkOrderId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n\n      const handleEditWorkOrderClose = () => {\n        setEditWorkOrderOpen(false);\n        setEditingWorkOrderId(null);\n        setWorkOrder({\n          title: '',\n          description: '',\n          status: 'Open',\n          assignedTo: '',\n          dueDate: '',\n          estimatedHours: 0\n        });\n      };\n\n      // Edit Work Order Handler - saves the edited work order data\n      const handleEditWorkOrderSave = async () => {\n        if (workOrder.title && workOrder.description && editingWorkOrderId) {\n            try {\n              await updateWorkOrders(editingWorkOrderId.toString(), workOrder);\n\n              // Update local state with the edited work order data\n              setWorkOrders((prev) => prev.map((wo) => (wo.id === editingWorkOrderId ? { ...wo, ...workOrder } : wo))); // string comparison\n              \n              handleEditWorkOrderClose();\n              setSnackbarMessage('Work order updated successfully');\n              setSnackbarOpen(true);\n            } catch (error) {\n              console.error('Failed to update work order:', error);\n              // Check if it's a version conflict\n              if (error.message && error.message.includes('409')) {\n                  setSnackbarMessage('Version conflict: Please try the update again.');\n              } else {\n                  setSnackbarMessage('Failed to update work order. Please try again.');\n              }\n\n              // Keep dialog open on error so user can retry\n              setSnackbarOpen(true);\n            }\n          }\n      };\n\n      // Edit Work Order Handler - opens the edit modal and populates it with the selected work order data\n      const handleEditWorkOrder = (workOrderToEdit: any) => {\n        setEditingWorkOrderId(workOrderToEdit.id);\n      \n        // Convert ISO datetime to datetime-local format for the input field\n        const dueDateLocal = workOrderToEdit.dueDate \n          ? new Date(workOrderToEdit.dueDate).toISOString().slice(0, 16)\n          : '';\n        \n        setWorkOrder({\n          title: workOrderToEdit.title,\n          description: workOrderToEdit.description,\n          status: workOrderToEdit.status,\n          assignedTo: workOrderToEdit.assignedTo,\n          dueDate: dueDateLocal,\n          estimatedHours: workOrderToEdit.estimatedHours\n        });\n        setEditWorkOrderOpen(true);\n      };\n\n      // Function to update work orders with version conflict handling\n      const updateWorkOrders = async (workOrderId: string, updatedWorkOrder: any): Promise<any> => {\n        try {\n          // First, fetch the latest work order data to get the current version\n          const latestWorkOrderData = await fetchWorkOrderData(workOrderId);\n\n          // Convert datetime-local format to ISO 8601 for backend\n          const dueDateISO = updatedWorkOrder.dueDate \n            ? new Date(updatedWorkOrder.dueDate).toISOString() \n            : updatedWorkOrder.dueDate;\n\n          // Now update with the latest data and correct version\n          const updatedData = {\n            ...latestWorkOrderData,\n            ...updatedWorkOrder,\n            dueDate: dueDateISO,\n          };\n\n          // Upsert the updated work order data\n          const data = await upsertWorkOrderData(updatedData);\n\n          console.log('Work Order Update Success:', data);\n\n          // Update local state with the server response data (which should include our changes)\n          if (data.objs && data.objs[0]) {\n            setWorkOrders((prev) => prev.map((wo) => (wo.id === workOrderId ? data.objs[0] : wo)));\n          } else {\n            // Fallback: manually update the work order if server doesn't return updated data\n            setWorkOrders((prev) =>\n              prev.map((wo) => (wo.id === workOrderId ? { ...wo, ...updatedWorkOrder } : wo))\n            );\n          }\n\n          return data;\n        } catch (error) {\n          console.error('Error updating work order data:', error);\n\n          if (error.message && error.message.includes('409')) {\n            console.error('Unexpected version conflict even after fetching latest data');\n          }\n\n          throw error; // Re-throw to handle in handleEditWorkOrderSave\n        }\n      };\n  \n//    return (\n//      ...\n//    );\n//  }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the return statement, add the following event handler to the `WorkOrderModal` component for editing work orders. \n\nAdditionally, add another WorkOrderModal component as a sibling. Since users will edit existing work orders with this modal, we will pre-populate the modal with the existing values of the work order when it's opened. To do this, we will set the `workOrder` state to the values of the work order we're trying to edit when the edit button is clicked. This way, when the modal opens, it will already be filled with the existing data of the work order.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         {/* 3. Details Tab: Shows metadata and additional information */}\n//         <Paper className=\"wt-tabs-paper\">\n//           ...\n             {/* Work Orders Tab */}\n//           {tabValue === 1 && (\n//             <WorkOrdersTab\n//              workOrders={workOrders}\n//              handleWorkOrderOpenModal={handleCreateWorkOrder}\n                handleEditWorkOrder={handleEditWorkOrder} \n//             />)}\n//         </Paper>\n//       </Container>\n//      </Box>\n\n//      {/* Create Work Order Modal */}\n//      ...\n\n//     {/* Snackbar */}\n//     ...\n\n        {/* Edit Work Order Modal */}\n        <WorkOrderModal\n          open={editWorkOrderOpen}\n          workOrder={workOrder}\n          onSave={handleEditWorkOrderSave}\n          onClose={handleEditWorkOrderClose}\n          onChange={handleWorkOrderChange}\n          onNumberChange={handleNumberChange}\n          isEdit={true}\n        />\n//       </>\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Verify results","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this section, you should be able to click the edit button on a work order, see a modal with the existing values of the work order, edit those values, and persist the changes to the back-end. \n\nUpdate the title of the work order you created in Part 2 to `Updated work order` and verify that the change is reflected in the UI after saving. \n\nYou can also verify that changes were persisted by running the following cell to fetch the `WorkOrder` with the updated title.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"WorkOrder.fetch({filter: Filter.eq('title', 'Updated work order')})","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"------","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 4: Delete work orders","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this last section, you'll add the last piece of the CRUD workflow on the turbine-specific page by implementing functionality to delete work orders.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 4.1 Add CRUD method to delete work orders","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Add the following function to <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD.ts\"><code>WorkOrderCRUD.ts</code></a>. This function hits the `WorkOrder#remove` API to delete a work order by its ID. The `remove` method expects `thisArg` to be a `WorkOrder` object stub (for example, `{ id: WT-42 }`), so the request body wraps the id in an object.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WorkOrderCRUD.ts\n*/\n\n// ...\n\nexport const deleteWorkOrder = async (id: string): Promise<any> => {\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WorkOrder/remove', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'x-request-envelope': 'true',\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      thisArg: { id },\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Failed to delete work order');\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n};","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Add the following imports to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>. We'll also import some new components from Material UI to add a confirmation dialog when deleting work orders.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\nimport { deleteWorkOrder } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WorkOrderCRUD';\nimport { Dialog, DialogTitle, DialogContent, DialogContentText, DialogActions, Button } from '@mui/material';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### 4.2 Implement the delete functionality","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now, we'll implement the delete functionality in the UI. When a user clicks the delete button on a work order, we want to show a confirmation dialog to confirm that they want to delete the work order. If they confirm, we will call the `deleteWorkOrder` function we just implemented to delete the work order.\n\nAdd the following code to <a href='../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx'><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>. This code accomplishes the following:\n\n- Initializes the state for the confirmation dialog and the ID of the work order to be deleted.\n- Handles opening and closing the confirmation dialog.\n- Calls the `deleteWorkOrder` function to delete the work order when the user confirms the deletion.    ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//    ...\n//    \n//    const updateWorkOrders = async (workOrderId: string, updatedWorkOrder: any): Promise<any> => {\n//      ...\n//    };\n\n      // DELETE CONFIRMATION\n      const [deleteConfirmOpen, setDeleteConfirmOpen] = useState(false);\n      const [deleteWorkOrderId, setDeleteWorkOrderId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n\n      const handleDeleteWorkOrder = async (id: string) => {\n        setWorkOrders((prev) => prev.filter((order) => order.id !== id));\n        await deleteWorkOrder(id);\n      };\n\n      const handleDeleteWorkOrderClick = (id: string) => {\n        setDeleteWorkOrderId(id);\n        setDeleteConfirmOpen(true);\n      };\n\n      const handleDeleteConfirmClose = () => {\n        setDeleteConfirmOpen(false);\n        setDeleteWorkOrderId(null);\n      };\n\n      const handleDeleteConfirm = async () => {\n        if (deleteWorkOrderId !== null) {\n          await handleDeleteWorkOrder(deleteWorkOrderId);\n          setSnackbarMessage('Work order deleted successfully');\n          setSnackbarOpen(true);\n        }\n        handleDeleteConfirmClose();\n      };\n\n//    return (\n//      ...\n//    );\n//  }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In the return statement, add a delete handler to the delete button in the `WorkOrdersTab` component. This handler will open the confirmation dialog and set the ID of the work order to be deleted.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//         ...\n//         {/* 3. Details Tab: Shows metadata and additional information */}\n//         <Paper className=\"wt-tabs-paper\">\n//           ...\n             {/* Work Orders Tab */}\n//           {tabValue === 1 && (\n//             <WorkOrdersTab\n//              workOrders={workOrders}\n//              handleWorkOrderOpenModal={handleCreateWorkOrder}\n//              handleEditWorkOrder={handleEditWorkOrder} \n                handleDeleteWorkOrder={handleDeleteWorkOrderClick}\n//             />)}\n//         </Paper>\n//       </Container>\n//      </Box>\n//\n//      ...\n//     </>\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Lastly, add the `Dialog` component as a sibling to the other components in the return statement. This will display the confirmation dialog when a user clicks the delete button on a work order.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n//  const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n//     ...\n//     return (\n//       <>\n//        ...\n//\n//        {/* Edit Work Order Modal */}\n//        ...\n//\n          {/* Delete Confirmation Dialog */}\n          <Dialog\n            open={deleteConfirmOpen}\n            onClose={handleDeleteConfirmClose}\n            aria-labelledby=\"delete-dialog-title\"\n            aria-describedby=\"delete-dialog-description\"\n          >\n            <DialogTitle id=\"delete-dialog-title\">\n              Confirm Delete\n            </DialogTitle>\n            <DialogContent>\n              <DialogContentText id=\"delete-dialog-description\">\n                Are you sure you want to delete this work order? This action cannot be undone.\n              </DialogContentText>\n            </DialogContent>\n            <DialogActions>\n              <Button onClick={handleDeleteConfirmClose} color=\"primary\">\n                  Cancel\n              </Button>\n              <Button onClick={handleDeleteConfirm} color=\"error\" variant=\"contained\" autoFocus>\n                  Delete\n              </Button>\n            </DialogActions>\n          </Dialog>\n//       </>\n//     );\n//   }","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Verify changes","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After implementing this section, try creating a new WorkOrder record, then try deleting it by selecting **Delete** on the WorkOrder card. You should see a confirmation dialog. After confirming the deletion, the WorkOrder record should be removed from the UI.\n\nAlternatively, if you delete the dummy `WorkOrder` record that you created in Part 2 and updated in Part 3, you should expect that the record is now deleted in the back-end. Run the following code snippet to verify that the record has been deleted.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"WorkOrder.fetch({filter: Filter.eq('title', 'Updated work order')})","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Summary","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"You added functionality to the turbine-specific page to fetch, create, update, and delete work orders. You should now have a good understanding of how to implement CRUD operations in your application and persist those changes to the back-end.\n\n<style>\n    .c3-a-alert {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: flex-start;\n      padding: 16px 20px;\n      gap: 8px;\n      align-self: stretch;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      border: 1px solid;\n      font-size: 14px;\n      font-style: normal;\n      font-weight: 400;\n      line-height: 150%;\n      margin-bottom: 20px;\n      width: auto;\n    }\n\n    .c3-a-alert-warning {\n      background-color: rgb(178,235,242);\n      border-color: rgb(0,96,100);\n      color: rgba(17, 17, 18, 0.95);\n    }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"c3-a-alert c3-a-alert-warning\">\n    <p>Congratulations, you completed the last course in the UI Development learning path! Remember to complete the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/build-a-data-management-interface/418650\" style=\"color: blue;\">quiz on C3 AI Academy</a>.</p>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div style=\"display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:16px; align-items:center; margin-top:24px;\">\n  <a href=\"./10-create-turbine-dashboard.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 10: Create a Turbine Dashboard\"\n     style=\"justify-self:start; display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #d0d7de; background:#f6f8fa; color:#0b1026; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    ← Previous: Create a Turbine Dashboard\n  </a>\n\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"7225b51f-8532-4579-b03c-2feeeee3ac97","appName":"academyui","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino"}}